article.headline: Barrett scores six in final 3:12 for Pirates
article.linkText: Seton Hall hands Rutgers second home loss
article.story: PISCATAWAY, N.J. (AP) -- Andre Barrett scored six of his 13 points in the final 3:12 and Seton Hall became the second opposing team to win at the Rutgers Athletic Center this season, defeating the Scarlet Knights 66-64 on Sunday. John Allen added 17 points and Andre Sweet had 16 and nine rebounds as the Pirates (20-8, 10-6 Big East) nailed down their first 20-win season since the 1999-2000 campaign, a year they reached the Sweet 16 in the NCAA tournanemt. Kelly Whitney added 13 points and 10 rebounds as Seton Hall ended the Scarlet Knights' eight-game winning streak at home and handed them their second home loss in 15 games. Rutgers (16-11, 7-9) had two chances to win the tight, hard-fought game in the closing seconds. Marquis Webb had a game-winning 3-point attempt bounce off the rim with just under 4 seconds to play. Sean Axani, who had an outstanding second half with 10 points and seven rebounds in his final home game, tapped the rebound out to the left wing. Ricky Shields' off-balance 30-footer at the buzzer wasn't even close. The victory gave Seton Hall a sweep of the two games against Rutgers this year and sent the Pirates into the Big East tournament in New York on Wednesday as the sixth seed. Seton Hall will play Villanova at 9 p.m., with the winner meeting Providence. Rutgers will play Virginia Tech. The winner will face top-seeded Pittsburgh. Quincy Douby led Rutgers with 15 points. Herve Lamizana had 14 points and seven assists. The final 7:31 was an exciting matchup of the two New Jersey rivals. After Whitney converted a three-point play to give the Pirates a 52-46 lead, the Scarlet Knights went on a 10-2 run with Lamizana making a steal and a big jam to give Rutgers a 56-54 lead, its first since the opening minute. The Pirates came right back with a 9-2 spurt. Sweet tied the game with a basket in the low post with 4:21 to go. Barrett gave Seton Hall the lead at 58-56 with two free throws with 3:12 to go, just seconds after the officials made no call on a collision between Lamizana and a Pirates player pushing the ball up the court. Allen extended the lead to 60-56 with a foul-line jumper with 2:26 to play, but Axani followed the second of two straight missed foul shots by Webb with a putback with 1:55 to play. After Barrett and Lamizana exchanged 3-pointers, Allen made two free throws to give Seton Hall a 65-61 lead with 33.7 seconds to go. Douby closed the gap to a point with a 3-pointer with 22.6 seconds left. Barrett made the end exciting, hitting the second of two free throws with 15.7 seconds left. However, Rutgers could not get its last two shots to fall.
